race.comment: SUPER SUNNY SEEYA (3) doesn't win out of turn but has been good in his two runs back without winning. Peaking now and will relish the extra 200m. Expect him to drift back from the draw and be taking big strides late. EXPLOSIVE STYLE (4) broke her maiden last start over 1000m at this track. Is lightly raced and has plenty of scope for improvement. No reason she cannot get the job done again. ACANTILADO (1) showed early speed from a good draw last time but failed to go on with the job at Seymour. Will push forward again and is helped under the big weight by Hill claiming 3kg. CHAIRMAN'S CHOICE (9) improved last start but found a couple better at Tumbarumba, beaten less than a length. Looks to be in the right race so he should be in contention again.
